This paper focuses on human-robot collaboration and knowledge representation for manipulations that can be performed by domestic robots. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of weights and success rates, which are common in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also considers the role of human assistants in the collaboration, which falls under the category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Additionally, the paper discusses the optimization of task trees, which can be considered a machine learning problem, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of the functional object-oriented network, which is a type of knowledge representation used in control systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) a possible category as well.
